      "summary": "Iranian director Asghar Farhadi, Spain's Pedro Almódovar, and Russia's Andrey Zvyagintsev are among 21 directors vying for the coveted Palme d'Or prize at the Cannes Film Festival on April 9. Festival director Thierry Frémaux revealed a list of films in the main competition, including three from Japan and three from Spain. Major Hollywood studios are not expected to be present at the event. Other frontrunners for the top prize include Japan's Hirokazu Kore-eda and Romania's Cristian Mungiu. The festival will also feature a surprising amount of football, documentaries about legendary forward Eric Cantona and the England-Argentina 1986 World Cup match.",
      "shortSummary": "Iranian director Asghar Farhadi and Spain's Pedro Almódovar will compete for the Cannes Palme d'Or, with major Hollywood studios and other notable films included.",
